+LAW-II "no fake working" gate. Codex iter-3 P0 + iter-4 P2 on the I-ux-001 plan:
+the demo bundle was unsigned and the UI could render "Signed bundle" from any
+.asc presence (placeholder or otherwise). Fixed:
+
+- Sign the real-data demo bundle (web/public/canonical_bundles/v1_canonical_success/)
+  with the CANONICAL Carney-demo signing key (Ed25519 FB221F...01CC, the one
+  pinned in state/polaris_gpg_keyid.txt and shipped at
+  docs/carney_handover/polaris_demo_pubkey.asc). End-to-end verified: a reviewer
+  importing only the shipped pubkey gets exit 0 + "Good signature."
+- Replace the placeholder test-fixture .asc with a real signature too.
+
+- LoadedBundle.signaturePresent (boolean) -> signatureState (tri-valued:
+  missing | present_unverified | gpg_verified). Server loader (web/lib/
+  gpg_verify_bundle.ts) runs gpg --verify in an ISOLATED keyring (--no-default-
+  keyring --keyring) so the host's default keyring cannot satisfy the check,
+  AND asserts the signing-key fingerprint matches the pinned canonical key.
+  Client loader returns at most present_unverified (no GPG in the browser).
+
+- SignatureBadge (bundle_header.tsx) accepts the tri-valued state. Only
+  gpg_verified shows the green "Signed bundle"; present_unverified shows
+  "Signature attached -- verify offline"; missing shows "Not signed -- trust
+  not established." Audit page rendering aligned.
+
+- build_canonical_demo_bundle.py now signs by default with the canonical key,
+  reading $POLARIS_GPG_HOMEDIR (~/.gnupg-polaris) + $POLARIS_GPG_KEY_ID (or
+  state/polaris_gpg_keyid.txt). Fails LOUDLY if the key is unavailable; never
+  silently falls back to the default keyring. --unsigned opt-out preserved.
+
+- New CI guard scripts/check_signed_bundles.py: enforces that every "must-be-
+  signed" bundle in the repo GPG-verifies against the shipped trust root +
+  signing-key fingerprint matches the pinned canonical key. Wired into
+  .github/workflows/web_ci.yml as required job check_signed_bundles. Prevents
+  the iter-3 P0 regression.
+
+- pytest tests/scripts/test_check_signed_bundles.py covers all three states
+  (signed-OK / missing .asc / placeholder .asc). 3/3 PASS locally.
+
+Smoke evidence: outputs/audits/I-ux-001a/gpg_verify_demo_bundle.txt
+Codex brief APPROVE iter 2 (zero P0, zero P1): .codex/I-ux-001a/codex_brief_verdict_iter2.txt
