+Codex iter 1 caught five real findings; all fixed:
+
+P0 — build script's `_sign_manifest_or_fail` was defined but never called from
+main() (and argparse/os/subprocess imports were missing). The script would
+silently regress the demo bundle to unsigned. Wired into main() + added the
+missing imports.
+
+P1 — server loader CWD: under Next.js process.cwd() is `web/`, not the repo
+root, so `docs/...` and `state/...` weren't found and every signed bundle
+degraded to present_unverified before GPG ever ran. Added `_findRepoRoot()`
+that resolves via $POLARIS_REPO_ROOT or walks up looking for the pinned-fp
+sentinel; both the trust-root and the pin file are now anchored to it.
+
+P1 — isolation defeated by host `use-keyboxd`. The smoke evidence literally
+showed "Specified keyrings are ignored due to option \"use-keyboxd\"" leaking
+in. Switched both the server loader and the CI guard to `gpgv` against a
+freshly-dearmored binary keyring built ONLY from the shipped trust root. gpgv
+is the dedicated verify-only tool: no agent spawn, no keyboxd, no host
+gpg.conf -- the only key it can trust is the one we pinned.
+
+P1 — CI guard path: web_ci.yml's default `working-directory: web` made
+`python scripts/check_signed_bundles.py` resolve to web/scripts/... which
+doesn't exist. Overrode `defaults.run.working-directory: .` on the
+check_signed_bundles job.
+
+P2 — workflow `paths:` filter didn't include the guard inputs (script, tests,
+fixture, trust-root pubkey, pinned fingerprint), so future regressions could
+bypass CI. Added all five.
+
+P2 — audit/page.tsx still said "pending sovereign signing" / "signer not yet
+live" — conflicted with the new gpg_verified state. Updated copy to point at
+the offline-verify command + the pinned-FP file.
+
+P3 — fixture README + client-loader doc comment updated to describe real
+signature + tri-valued state.
+
