The foundation doc for the §14 step-1 work of the Codex-APPROVED I-ux-001
plan. Locks the concrete craft bar that iter-1 / iter-2 of the plan review
flagged as "not specific enough for Linear/Stripe-tier":

- Type scale: Geist, 8-step scale, measure 62-72ch for brief prose, tabular
  numerals on every count display.
- Color = meaning only, with TWO INDEPENDENT semantic palettes (the
  two-judgment separation from plan §0/§4):
  - Faithfulness: verified (green) / partial (amber) / unsupported (red).
  - Evidence-strength: ordinal slate-blue (high → very-low).
  - Distinct families so the eye never conflates "supported by source"
    with "evidence is strong" (the lethal clinical confusion).
- Brand red `#c8102e` operator-LOCKED, action+identity only.
- 8px space rhythm; comfortable vs compact density modes per-surface.
- Motion: 3 durations (120/200/320ms), one easing (`ease-standard`),
  honest (state-communication, not decoration), prefers-reduced-motion
  honored everywhere.
- Six microstates (default/hover/focus/active/disabled/loading) mandatory
  on every interactive element.
- Crisp SVG maple-leaf spec (replaces "low-fidelity dot-cloud").
- Trust copy table (de-jargons "two-family invariant", "POOL ID",
  "Signature missing"); single source of truth in web/lib/trust_copy.ts.

Spec only — no code yet. Subsequent per-page Issues consume the tokens
incrementally; the audit + visual review on each page is the validation.

