Implements §4 of the Codex-APPROVED I-ux-001 plan + §12 of the tokens v2:
"motion communicates state, never decorates" (Vercel guideline) +
two-judgment separation kept visually orthogonal at every beat.

Specifies:
- Stage 0 resting state: hairline underline (faithfulness) + leading margin
  certainty dot (evidence strength) — two affordances, two color families,
  never adjacent.
- Stage 1 focus/hover peek (alpha bump only, no panel).
- Stage 2 the 6-beat reveal (claim → faithfulness → evidence strength
  → source span → signature → "what this does NOT prove" disclosure),
  with per-beat durations + easings + token references. Total
  time-to-first-proof < 400ms.
- Stage 3 in-place claim switching (J/K, < 120ms perceived).
- Stage 4 mobile bottom-sheet (75vh, swipe + drag).
- Stage 5 reduced-motion equivalent (instant state swap; sequencing
  INTENT preserved as visual hierarchy).
- Stage 6 failure-state choreography per plan §6:
  missing/present_unverified signature, UNSUPPORTED claim, inadequacy
  refusal — all honest.
- Stage 7 Home teaser: compact inline 6-beat for a real claim, plays
  on click without sign-in. The 30-second "I've never seen research I
  could check like this" moment.
- Stage 8 plan-§15 interaction-acceptance Playwright trace tests.

Pre-built ASCII frames at each stage so a reader can see the layout
before any pixels exist. Spec only — no code. Implementation is
subsequent per-page Issues.

