brand red #c8102e (oklch 0.53 0.21 22) -- clinical user could confuse
"unsupported claim alarm" with "primary CTA". Re-picked --unsupported to
hue 320 (magenta-red), 60+ degrees from brand. Added a binding hue-band
rule: brand 0-40, unsupported 300-340, no token may sit in either band.

P1: storyboard total reads 700ms, conflicting with the stated <400ms
target. Clarified that <400ms is "time-to-first-proof" (Beat 2 visible at
250ms), NOT total reveal. Total 700ms is fine because the user reads as
beats paint; the answer lands first.

P1: home teaser used fabricated claim text. Replaced with the actual
first verified sentence from web/public/canonical_bundles/v1_canonical_success/
verified_report.json — the real claim the home page will render. Same
fix in Stage 0 illustration.

P1: six microstates were "deferred to components_catalogue.md" which
didn't exist. Wrote the catalogue with the minimum Codex required:
ClaimSentence, ProofPanel, FaithfulnessChip, CertaintyBadge, SourceCard,
SignaturePill, WhatThisDoesNotProve, IntendedUseBanner, plus a shared
interactive baseline (six microstates × concrete CSS contract) every
component inherits. The wiring table at the end maps each storyboard
surface to its components, so no element is "assumed" anymore.

P2: added --verified-fg / --partial-fg / --unsupported-fg foreground
tokens so chip text on the tint backgrounds passes WCAG-AA without
implementations having to derive their own.

