From 08e7b464b95061b7f794088d3a5bb35435fd759f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: msn <msn@polaris.dev>
Date: Sun, 24 May 2026 03:16:40 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 5/7] I-ux-001b (#876): fix Codex iter-2 P1s (catalogue
 scope+spinner, certainty fg per level) + P2s (Beat 4 timing,
 SourceSpanPreview spec)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

P1 #1 [catalogue baseline scoped only to .btn, spinner invisible]:
- Rewrote the shared interactive contract to target `.interactive` +
  every relevant tag/role selector (button, [role=button], a[href],
  summary, .btn, .link, .chip[role=button], sentence affordances).
- Fixed loading: hide label via `visibility: hidden` on children (not
  `color: transparent`), so the spinner border using --foreground stays
  visible; reduced-motion shows a non-spinning indicator dot.
- Encoded the focus-visible offset directly in the box-shadow stack so
  the undefined --ring-offset token from iter-1 P3 is no longer named.

P1 #2 [certainty-fg only worked for dark levels]:
- Replaced single --certainty-fg with per-level foreground tokens
  (--certainty-{high,moderate,low,very-low}-fg). Dark backgrounds use
  near-white (≥4.7:1 AA), light backgrounds use near-black (≥6.3:1 AAA).
- Added a binding "foreground-by-level rule" so CertaintyBadge reads
  --certainty-<level>-fg directly, never the (now intentionally absent)
  --certainty-fg.

P2 [Beat 4 highlight 200ms vs ≤150ms target]:
- Storyboard Beat 4 now specifies --motion-fast (120ms) for the mask
  reveal, meeting the ≤150ms spec.

P2 [SourceSpanPreview referenced but never specified]:
- Added §5a SourceSpanPreview entry to the catalogue: props, phrase-
  grouped highlight (not pink tiles), mask-reveal at --motion-fast,
  auto-scroll, reduced-motion handling, a11y (region role + mark labels
  + 400% zoom support).
- Wired into §10 mapping with the §5a reference.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
