P1 #1 [loading rules only target .btn/.link/.interactive — bare button or
[role=button] get pointer-events:none with NO spinner]: expanded the
loading child-hide AND ::after spinner selectors to include button,
[role="button"], a[aria-busy], summary[aria-busy]. Same for the
reduced-motion override. Every selector in the baseline group now gets
the full loading contract.

P1 #2 [CertaintyBadge spec text still said --certainty-fg AND moderate
contrast was 4.48:1 (under AA 4.5:1)]: catalogue text now reads
`var(--certainty-<level>-fg)`. Tokens bumped --certainty-moderate
lightness 0.56 -> 0.50 to recover WCAG AA on the near-white foreground
(now ≥4.6:1).

P2 [SourceSpanPreview prop union missed `unsupported` even though
storyboard Stage 6 requires showing the span for UNSUPPORTED claims]:
extended `spans[].faithfulness` and `tint` to include "unsupported", with
the documented behavior (leading XCircle outside the mark, "this is
what they cited — and it doesn't contain the claim" semantic).

P3 [--ring-offset still referenced in tokens doc but undefined]: added
explicit note that focus-visible spacing is encoded in the box-shadow
stack; no --ring-offset token exists.

